title: Mayday.Air.Crash.Investigations.S02.E06.Missing.Over.New.York.DV
description:
Missing Over New York

Aired on 02/27/2005, Narrated by Jonathan Aris

On 25 January 1990, Avianca Flight 52, a Boeing 707-320B, on a flight to New York from Colombia, is delayed numerous times by bad weather en route and is dangerously low on fuel as it attempts a landing. Wind shear forces the crew to abort the approach just one mile from the runway. They initiate a go-around, but are directed back into a holding pattern by air traffic controllers unaware of the low-fuel situation. The Boeing 707 then runs out of fuel, causing it to crash on Long Island near New York.
